verbose_text: When proliferating myoblasts must withdraw from the cell cycle to differentiate, growth factors, such as HGF and bFGF, which stimulate cell cycle progression, regulate the activity of myogenic regulatory transcription factors, such as MyoD, myogenic factor 5 (Myf5), myogenin and myogenic regulatory factor (MRF) 4, that have been shown to control the specification and differentiation of the muscle lineage.
